# Test fixture provenance

These fixtures live under `tests/` and are NOT installed or shipped in the
package (`inst/`); they exist only to drive the offline test suite.

Unless noted otherwise below, every fixture in this directory is
**sitemapr-authored, clean-room** content created for this project and is
covered by the package license (MIT). The XML/text files describe synthetic
`example.com` sitemaps; they reproduce no third-party document.

## Schema-validation fixtures (Layer C)

Authored for the schema-validation slice (SITE-qcjvesdw). Each exercises a
specific resolution/validation path against the bundled clean-room XSD
profiles; none is copied or adapted from an upstream corpus.

| Fixture | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `valid-minimal.xml` | minimal valid core `urlset` |
| `valid-index.xml` | valid core `sitemapindex` |
| `schema-invalid-urlset.xml` | misplaced `<priority>` before `<loc>` (invalid) |
| `ns-image.xml` | core + image extension |
| `ns-news.xml` | core + news extension |
| `ns-video.xml` | core + video extension |
| `ns-hreflang.xml` | core + xhtml:link hreflang alternates |
| `ns-all-four.xml` | core + image + video + news + hreflang (runtime profile) |
| `ns-video-invalid-in-mixed.xml` | valid siblings, invalid video child (scoping) |
| `ns-unknown.xml` | namespace absent from the catalog |
| `xxe-attempt.xml` | external SYSTEM entity; must not expand |

## Imported corpus (`corpus/`)

The `corpus/` subdirectory is the fixture set imported wholesale from the
sibling **sitemap-validator** project (SITE-uivyzfhe) to broaden coverage and
serve as a shared golden reference across the two ports. The files are
byte-identical to sitemap-validator's `fixtures/` tree, preserving its layout
(`xml/`, `text/`, `hreflang/`, `encoding/`, `compressed/`) and names so the same
inputs can be run through both implementations and their outcomes compared.

Both projects are authored by the same maintainer; every corpus fixture is
clean-room synthetic `example.com` content reproducing no third-party document,
and is likewise covered by the package license (MIT). The `compressed/` archives
were built from the same synthetic sources.

`tests/testthat/test-corpus-fixtures.R` drives every corpus fixture through
`validate_sitemap()` and snapshots the per-fixture finding codes (or the classed
`sitemapr_*` error, for documented limitations: corrupt/tar archives, UTF-16,
malformed/empty XML) as `_snaps/corpus-fixtures.md` — the golden map.

sitemap-validator also ships a ~52 MB "kitchen-sink" generator that emits one
document exercising every protocol/hreflang code. It is *not* imported: it
exceeds the repo's 5 MB commit guard, and sitemapr already covers the equivalent
runtime-generation cases in-memory (e.g. the 50 000-entry over-cap urlset built
by `vp_urlset_with_n()` in `setup-steps-validate-protocol.R`).
